- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the need for empirical research standards in cybersecurity and proposes a research tool to aid in experimentation. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also likely as the paper discusses the development of research best practices in cybersecurity. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is a possible category as the paper may touch on the interaction between humans and cybersecurity systems. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is another possible category as the paper discusses the importance of scientific integrity and reputability in cybersecurity research. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a less likely category, but may be relevant if the paper discusses the use of AI in cybersecurity simulations.
